<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFF4014863A5F32492FD8E79" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFF4014863A5F324917E88F9" blockId="22.[151,760,804,1371]" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF4014863A5F32492688819" bold="true" box="[151,281,804,827]" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Comments.</emphasis>
The number of specimens and sex was not specified in the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF401486108F34493B98859" authorityName="Duvivier" authorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suturalis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF401486108F34493B98859" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Platyxantha suturalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The Duvivier’s collection in the ISNB contains only one female which well fits the description. Because there is no evidence about more specimens in the description I treat this specimen as the 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF401486298F3C4917A88F9" box="[426,523,964,987]" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="84585F48FFF401486387F3E492FD8E79" blockId="22.[151,760,804,1371]" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">
Since the description of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF4014862F6F3E491DD88D9" authorityName="Duvivier" authorityYear="1885" box="[452,684,996,1019]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suturalis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF4014862F6F3E491DD88D9" box="[452,684,996,1019]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Platyxantha suturalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it was listed only in catalogues. While 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF4014862EFF40491168F39" author="WEISE J." box="[477,615,1028,1051]" editor="SCHENKLING S." firstAuthor="WEISE" journalOrPublisher="Berlin" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 225" refId="ref33576" refString="WEISE J. 1924: Pars 78: Chrysomelidae: 13. Galerucinae. In: SCHENKLING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus. W. Junk, Berlin, pp. 1 - 225." title="Pars 78: Chrysomelidae: 13. Galerucinae" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Coleopterorum Catalogus" year="1924">WEISE (1924)</bibRefCitation>
classified it in 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF4014863A5F42491418F19" authority=", WILCOX (1973)" authorityName=", WILCOX" authorityYear="1973" box="[151,560,1060,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Haplotes">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF4014863A5F42492648F19" box="[151,277,1060,1083]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Platyxantha</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF401486211F42492F08F19" box="[291,385,1060,1083]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Haplotes</emphasis>
), 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF4014862A6F42491418F19" author="WILCOX J. A." box="[404,560,1060,1083]" editor="WILCOX J. A." firstAuthor="WILCOX" journalOrPublisher="Editio seconda. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" pagination="433 - 664" refId="ref33616" refString="WILCOX J. A. 1973: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae: Luperini: Luperina. In: WILCOX J. A. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 78 (3). Editio seconda. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage, pp. 433 - 664." title="Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae: Luperini: Luperina" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 78 (3)." year="1973">WILCOX (1973)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF40148616CF42491898F19" author="KIMOTO S." box="[606,760,1060,1083]" firstAuthor="KIMOTO" journalOrPublisher="Kurume University Journal" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" pagination="201 - 237" part="39" refId="ref31701" refString="KIMOTO S. 1990: Check-list of Chrysomelidae of south east Asia, south of Thailand and west of Irian-Jaya of Indonesia, VI. Galerucinae, 2. Kurume University Journal 39: 201 - 237." title="Check-list of Chrysomelidae of south east Asia, south of Thailand and west of Irian-Jaya of Indonesia, VI. Galerucinae, 2." type="journal article" year="1990">KIMOTO (1990)</bibRefCitation>
listed it in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF40148625DF44492A58F79" authorityName=", MOHAMEDSAID" authorityYear="1998" box="[367,468,1092,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Polexima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF40148625DF44492A58F79" box="[367,468,1092,1115]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Polexima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both 
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF40148612BF44491088F79" box="[537,633,1092,1115]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Haplotes</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF401486199F44493C98F59" authorityName=", MOHAMEDSAID" authorityYear="1998" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Polexima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF401486199F44493C98F59" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Polexima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belong to the African fauna, Asian species previously listed in these genera were transferred elsewhere (often to 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF401486384F4A4925F8F99" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1814" box="[182,302,1188,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taumacera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF401486384F4A4925F8F99" box="[182,302,1188,1211]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Taumacera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Since only the female is known which considerably complicates the correct generic placement, I tentatively transfer 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF40148624AF4E4912C8FD9" authorityName="Duvivier" authorityYear="1885" box="[376,605,1252,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suturalis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF40148624AF4E4912C8FD9" box="[376,605,1252,1275]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Platyxantha suturalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF4014861B3F4E491898FD9" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1814" box="[641,760,1252,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taumacera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF4014861B3F4E491898FD9" box="[641,760,1252,1275]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Taumacera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the structure of the pronotum and antennae. However, the definite position can only be confirmed when the male is discovered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
